But more dangerous than meth,

00:09:52.005 --> 00:09:56.125
there was another product that CJNG made its future.

00:09:56.125 --> 00:09:58.324
A product that was so deadly

00:09:58.324 --> 00:10:02.125
that a person's life could be ended with just 2 mg.

00:10:02.125 --> 00:10:03.885
I will talk about this in the next video.

00:10:03.885 --> 00:10:05.444
But before that, the question is:

00:10:05.444 --> 00:10:09.085
how did the cartels in Mexico become so powerful

00:10:09.085 --> 00:10:11.444
that they could collide with the government?

00:10:11.444 --> 00:10:13.804
Imagine a Mexican mayor

00:10:13.804 --> 00:10:16.365
whose salary is 30,000 pesos a month.

00:10:16.365 --> 00:10:18.725
One night, an SUV arrives at his house.

00:10:18.725 --> 00:10:20.725
The cartel men are sitting inside.

00:10:20.725 --> 00:10:22.324
In one hand is a briefcase

00:10:22.324 --> 00:10:24.005
with 500,000 pesos in it.

00:10:24.005 --> 00:10:25.924
And in the other hand is a gun.

00:10:25.924 --> 00:10:29.605
The cartel men give the Mayor a choice: Plata o Plomo.

00:10:30.485 --> 00:10:32.485
It means either take the money

00:10:32.485 --> 00:10:33.404
or take the bullet.

00:10:33.404 --> 00:10:35.204
This is not an imaginary story.

00:10:35.204 --> 00:10:37.005
This scenario is repeated every week and every month

00:10:37.005 --> 00:10:39.245
in hundreds of cities across Mexico.

00:10:39.245 --> 00:10:41.164
How do you think this system was established?

00:10:41.164 --> 00:10:43.764
It was founded by a political party,

00:10:43.764 --> 00:10:45.005
the PRI.

00:10:45.005 --> 00:10:48.684
It was called the Institutional Revolutionary Party in English.

00:10:48.684 --> 00:10:51.965
This party ruled Mexico for 71 years

00:10:51.965 --> 00:10:54.105
as a single-party state.

00:10:54.105 --> 00:10:56.505
From 1929 to 2000,

00:10:56.505 --> 00:10:58.865
the central government under the PRI was so weak

00:10:58.865 --> 00:11:01.324
that instead of ending organized crime,

00:11:01.324 --> 00:11:03.324
it started making deals with them.

00:11:03.324 --> 00:11:05.125
This was called the Plaza System.

00:11:05.125 --> 00:11:15.929
The rules were very simple: the cartels would limit public violence, they wouldn't threaten PRI officials, and in return, everyone from mayors to governors would be given a mordida,

00:11:15.929 --> 00:11:16.929
which means a bribe.

00:11:16.929 --> 00:11:18.929
Imagine,

00:11:18.929 --> 00:11:20.929
the entire country was essentially on a weekly payroll.

00:11:20.929 --> 00:11:22.929
In the year 2000, when the PRI's reign ended,

00:11:22.929 --> 00:11:24.929
the entire system was shattered.

00:11:24.929 --> 00:11:26.929
In 2006, President Felipe Calderón

00:11:26.929 --> 00:11:28.929
declared war on the cartels.

00:11:28.929 --> 00:11:33.329
I say this is a fight of all Mexicans, because criminals don't discriminate.

00:11:33.329 --> 00:11:35.169
They hurt all of society.

00:11:35.169 --> 00:11:37.169
Thousands of soldiers were deployed,

00:11:37.169 --> 00:11:38.529
and with the help of the US,

00:11:38.529 --> 00:11:44.529
25 of Mexico's top 37 drug kingpins were killed or arrested.

00:11:44.529 --> 00:11:46.849
But the problem with this war on drugs was that

00:11:46.849 --> 00:11:50.049
if one drug leader was killed, another would take his place.

00:11:50.049 --> 00:11:52.609
If one kingpin was removed, two more would emerge.

00:11:52.609 --> 00:11:57.009
This led to the birth of smaller and more dangerous gangs.

00:11:57.009 --> 00:12:04.049
They toppled drug kingpins and hit cartels so hard that many shattered into smaller, ultra-violent gangs.

00:12:04.049 --> 00:12:10.049
Because of the increasing violence, Andrés Manuel López Obrador became president in 2018.

00:12:10.049 --> 00:12:12.049
He is known as AMLO.

00:12:12.049 --> 00:12:15.329
He introduced a new slogan: Hugs Not Bullets.

00:12:15.329 --> 00:12:19.009
Meaning that they would not use bullets, but would clean the system with empathy.

00:12:19.009 --> 00:12:24.849
He said that if we stop fighting with cartels and end poverty and unemployment, then crime will automatically reduce.

00:12:24.849 --> 00:12:30.289
We will change the failed strategy of combating insecurity and violence.

00:12:30.289 --> 00:12:31.929
Rather than using force,

00:12:31.929 --> 00:12:36.209
we will address the root causes of insecurity and violence.

00:12:36.209 --> 00:12:39.969
But unfortunately, the implementation failed.

00:12:39.969 --> 00:12:41.929
Neither did the war work, nor did the root causes get the attention they needed.

00:12:41.929 --> 00:12:44.129
And there was something else behind it.

00:12:44.129 --> 00:12:46.369
The most shocking thing about this whole story is that

00:12:46.369 --> 00:12:48.449
while Americans were the victims of the drug trade,

00:12:48.449 --> 00:12:52.289
America was also the architect of the drug crisis itself.

00:12:52.289 --> 00:12:53.969
And this was not because of one mistake,

00:12:53.969 --> 00:12:56.229
but a chain of repeated mistakes

00:12:56.229 --> 00:12:59.529
where America continually shot itself in the foot.

00:12:59.529 --> 00:13:01.109
In the early 1980s,

00:13:01.109 --> 00:13:05.969
the CIA supported Contra rebels against the socialist government of Nicaragua.

00:13:05.969 --> 00:13:09.829
The Contras received training and money through Mexican drug cartels.

